attributes.Long form description: The students dissasembles the table by first unscrewing each leg of the top shelf with the allen wrench. Then he unscrews each leg of the bottom shelf using  also the allen wrench. Once this is done he places all the pieces of the furniture on the table.

attributes.Transcription: Hello, thank you for being part of our study in front of us you'll see a nightstand from IKEA. That's for now.
Your task for now will be please, disassemble it.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the hex-socketed head of the first leg.

attributes.Transcription: First, please lay the nightstand up on the table.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: First the student had to lay the nightstand on the table before unscrewing.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the hex-socketed head of the second leg.
The student unscrews the hex-socketed head of the third leg.
The student unscrews the hex-socket head of the fourth leg.
The student withdraws the black top shelf.
The student disassembles the first leg from the bottom shelf.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student must first rotate the furniture.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the second leg from the bottom shelf.
The student disassembles the third leg from the bottom shelf.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student must start on the other side.

attributes.Transcription: I said it is on the shorter side.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the fourth leg from the bottom shelf.

attributes.Transcription: Thank you very much for everything for this task.
You may now press the stop button.
